# Development Setup

## Prerequisites

- Python {{ python_requires }}
- [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) package manager
- Git

## Clone and Install

```bash
git clone https://github.com/{{ github_owner }}/{{ github_repo }}.git
cd {{ project_slug }}
uv sync --all-packages
```

{% if with_pre_commit %}
## Install Git Hooks

```bash
uv run poe hooks
```

This installs pre-commit hooks that automatically run on each commit to ensure code quality.
{% endif %}

## IDE Setup

### VS Code

Install recommended extensions:

- Python
- Ruff
- Even Better TOML

### PyCharm

1. Set the Python interpreter to the virtual environment in `.venv/`
2. Enable Ruff integration in Settings → Tools → Ruff

## Environment Variables

Copy the example environment file:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Configure any required environment variables for your development needs.
